### ppOpen-MATH/VIS ver.0.2.0 ###

***********************************************************************************
1. Descriptions
This directory contains ppOpen-MATH/VIS (ver.0.2.0),
and sample codes with data sets. ppOpen-MATH/VIS is a set of libraries
for parallel visualization. 

Capabilities of ppOpen-MATH/VIS (ver.0.2.0) are as follows:

- Using background voxels with adaptive mesh refinement (AMR)
- Single UCD file
- Flat MPI parallel programming models
  (OpenMP/MPI hybrid will be supported in the future)
- Can be called from programs written in both of Fortran 90 and C
- Only FDM-type structured meshes are supported

(New in ver.0.2.0)
Number of vertices in UCD file is much fewer (less then 20%) than
that of ver.0.1.0.

***********************************************************************************
2. Directories

   * $(CUR): current directory

   $(CUR)/src                      : source code files of ppOpen-MATH/VIS
   $(CUR)/examples/FDM/src         : source code files of sample FDM code (fdm_test) 
                                     using ppOpen-MATH/VIS (one variable version)
   $(CUR)/examples/FDM/run         : sample data sets of fdm_test
   $(CUR)/examples/FDM/run/ppohVIS : directory storing UCD files
   $(CUR)/examples/FDM/run/results : directory storing sample results

   $(CUR)/examples/FDM3/src         : source code files of sample FDM code (fdm_test) 
                                      using ppOpen-MATH/VIS (three variable version)
   $(CUR)/examples/FDM3/run         : sample data sets of fdm_test
   $(CUR)/examples/FDM3/run/ppohVIS : directory storing UCD files
   $(CUR)/examples/FDM3/run/results : directory storing sample results

   $(CUR)/include: directory which stores created module files
   $(CUR)/lib    :                                libraries
   $(CUR)/bin    :                                exec. files

   $(CUR)/etc    : samples of 'Makefile.in'
   $(CUR)/doc    : documents

***********************************************************************************
3. Quick Start

(1) Preparation

 - C and Fortran 90 compliers
   (Operations have been confirmed by Intel, PGI, Fujitsu compilers)
 - MPI library

(2) Modify 'Makefile.in', samples are found in $(CUR)/etc
  $(CUR)/etc/Makefile.in.fx10   : Flat MPI for Fujitsu FX10
  $(CUR)/etc/Makefile.in.general:              Intel Compiler

   $(CC)         : C compiler with MPI
   $(COPTFLAGS)  : Optimization options for C compiler
   $(CXX)        : C++ compiler with MPI
   $(CXXOPTFLAGS): Optimization options for C++ compiler
   $(FC)         : F77 compiler with MPI
   $(FCOPTFLAGS) : Optimization options for F77 compiler
   $(F90)        : F90 compiler with MPI
   $(F90OPTFLAGS): Optimization options for F90 compiler

   $(PREFIX)/include   : directory that holds the installed module files
   $(PREFIX)/lib       :                                    libraries
   $(PREFIX)/bin       :                                    exec. files

 *** NOTICE ***: $(PREFIX) directory must be specified as ABSOLUTE/FULL path.

(3) Complile/install ppOpen-MATH/VIS and examples
 $>  cd $(CUR)/
 $>  make                 -> ppOpen-MATH/VIS
                             $<CUR>/lib/libppohvisfdm3d.a
                             $<CUR>/lib/libfppohvisfdm3d.a

 $>  make install         -> Install libraries to the destination
                             $<PREFIX>/lib/libppohvisfdm3d.a
                             $<PREFIX>/lib/libfppohvisfdm3d.a

(4) Compile/install "fdm_test" 
 $>  cd $(CUR)/

(one variable version)
 $>  make fdm1            -> fdm_test
                             $<CUR>/example/FDM/run/fdm_test
(three variable version)
 $>  make fdm3            -> fdm_test
                             $<CUR>/example/FDM3/run/fdm_test

 *** NOTICE ***: Process (4) must be done after (3).

(5) Running the code

(one variable version)
 $>  cd $(CUR)/examples/FDM/run
 $>  mpirun -np 8 fdm_test (or corresponding operations)
 $>  (UCD files are created in $(CUR)/examples/FDM/run/ppohVIS)

(three variable version)
 $>  cd $(CUR)/examples/FDM3/run
 $>  mpirun -np 8 fdm_test (or corresponding operations)
 $>  (UCD files are created in $(CUR)/examples/FDM3/run/ppohVIS)

(6) Clean/Unistall
 $>  cd $(CUR)/
 $>  make clean          -> Clean files
 $>  make unistall       -> Delete all installed files and directories

 $>  make fdm1_clean     -> Clean files
 $>  make fdm3_clean     -> Clean files

***********************************************************************************
